The paper deals with a problem of partitioning active users in a multi-access channel, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) concepts. The paper also uses random coding and decoding techniques, which are commonly used in information theory and machine learning (cs.LG). The problem of partitioning can also be seen as a combinatorial optimization problem, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of partitioning compared to group testing, which is related to statistical inference (cs.SI).
